# Patch for foundation-frontend/src/components/Layout.tsx
#
# Footer cleanup, reviewed from the user screenshot:
#
#   1. Remove "Corporate / CSR" footer link. It currently points to
#      /contact, i.e. it's not a real CSR landing page. Remove it rather
#      than leave a confusing stub. Add back when (and if) a dedicated
#      /corporate page is built, after the trust has MCA CSR-1
#      registration.
#
#   2. Add "Cookies" under LEGAL. The /cookies route already exists in
#      App.tsx; the link was simply missing from the footer.
#
#   3. Render registered office address under the tagline in the brand
#      column, backed by legal.registered_address from site_settings so
#      admins can edit it without a deploy.
#
#   4. Render a thin "registration badges" strip directly above the
#      bottom bar, driven by legal.registration_{80g,12a,fcra,csr1,pan}
#      from site_settings. Each badge is rendered conditionally — a key
#      with an empty value simply does not appear — so the strip
#      gracefully degrades to zero badges on day one and grows as the
#      admin fills in documents. This is independent of the existing
#      `useRegistrationInfo` hook, which continues to drive the prose
#      disclosure line next to the copyright.
#
# Layout.tsx is in the uncommitted set, so this change is kept as a
# patch rather than a direct edit. Apply AFTER V33 has been re-applied
# (or the new keys added manually), otherwise the five new config
# lookups will all resolve to empty strings and the new UI will just be
# blank. That's safe but defeats the point of the change.
#
# Usage:
#   cd <repo root>
#   git apply patches/0003-layout-tsx-footer-cleanup.patch
#
# If the hunks don't apply cleanly because of nearby in-flight edits,
# apply the changes by hand from this file.
#
